node.text:
We're kicking off our first est film production with a momentous Malvern Home renovation by @dohertydesignstudio from est magazine issue #35.
.
Tapping into its rich architectural past and 1980s new wave bones, @dohertydesignstudio have skilfully commandeered an epic journey to reinvent this Melbourne family home. An original 1980's design by architect Peter McIntyre. .
.
Experience the entire home via the link in profile or read the full feature in est magazine issue #35. .
.
Design @dohertydesignstudio
Building design @arialexander
Builder @north_building_group 
Styling @heathernetteking 
Florals and assitant styling @rachelpolivkastylist 
Art consultant @gb.art.consulting 
Landscape design @benscott_design 
Videography @richardlipp.studio
Words @meganmayrawson
Art @tompolo @liamsnootle @anyapesce @oocaleb @davidjamesgriggs @christianthompsonartist #leekyoung-hwa 
Furniture & Objects @domoaustralia @lightlydesign @loomtowels @fenton_and_fenton @abode_living @moderntimesau @ajarfurniture @lamarzoccohomeau

node.text:
Great land. Great architecture. Great living. In an est exclusive, we feature three unique films by Rob Mills Architecture & Interiors (RMA). Australian-based RMA’s latest project, a ground-breaking residence in Byron Bay incorporates Mill’s signature use of drama, curves, lines, light and a reflection of the qualities of the land.
.
View all three films via link in profile.
.
Videography @collider__
Creative Direction | Design @robmillsarchitects

ARCHITECTURE Chiswick House
​.
​In keeping with London Studio @foundassociates' sensitive and sympathetic alteration and addition projects, the Chiswick House sees a four-storey, double-fronted Edwardian reestablish a connection with its rear garden. 
​.
A wall of glass invites the greenery inside the contemporary rear pavilion, featuring the open plan living, dining and kitchen area where the family congregate.
​.
​Design @foundassociates
​Photography @huftonandcrow
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/

node.text:
DESIGNER INTERVIEW | Celebrating 21 Years of Mim Design 
​.
​"The moment you choose to say in your career, 'I actually want to enjoy the process', and enjoy a client relationship or enjoy working with another creative, you get a better result. When everyone is invested, you work on delivering an amazing project, but you also really enjoy the experience. Collaboration enables me to enjoy what I do."
​– Mim Fanning
​.
​In anticipation of the release of Mim Fanning’s retrospective book ‘Works’, we sat down with the Melbourne interior designer to recognise 21 years of her practice, @mimdesignstudio, and how it’s shaped the Australian design landscape.
​.
​Read more about Mim's retrospective 'Works' recognises this milestone – and her biggest feats and learnings – on estliving.com – link in profile. 
​.
​Design @mimdesignstudio 
​Photography @tfadtomferguson, @peterclarkephoto, @blachford & @davekulesza 
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/21-years-mim-design/

node.text:
ARCHIPRODUCTS DESIGN AWARDS | Nominate Your Favourite Design Product in 2021
​.
​For the first time, we're proud to announce we're the official Australian media partner of the 2021 @archiproducts Design Awards.
​.
​Hosted by architecture and design resource Archiproducts, the awards puts design on a global stage to recognise, reward and celebrate excellence across a broad range of categories.
​.
​An impressive list of more than 60 judges across 14 categories includes @harrynuriev,  @chrissa.amuah, @rossana_orlandi, @bobby, @eyeswoon, @quincocesdrago, @giorgiodona and @hesrawe.
​.
​Entries for the ADAs must be submitted by the 16th September 2021, with both longlisted products and winners announced between October and November 2021.
​.
Pictured: Anim bathtub by @salvatori_official, 2020 Archiproducts Design Award winner.
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/archiproducts-design-awards/

node.text:
HOME TOUR | A Heritage Transformation Inspired by the Australian Landscape
​.
​Interior designer @edwina__glenn transforms a classic Victorian into a present-day urban retreat in this elegant, highly personalised contemporary city home.
​.
We spoke with Edwina on introducing high-end finishes, premium appliances and design classics to this Victorian home – that all reveal a shared philosophy between designer and client of ‘buy once, buy well’.
​.
​Edwina remodelled the home's kitchen flow for efficiency, making way for an integrated, open-plan layout and appliances from @mieleaustralia, for their sustainability, reliability and longevity. 
​.
​Read more about how @edwina__glenn brought this character-filled home into the present via the link in profile. 
​.
​Design and styling @edwina__glenn 
Photography @sharyncairns⁣
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/heritage-transformation-edwina-glenn/

AT HOME WITH | Evelyn Moreels 
​.
​The Model House, home to interior designer Evelyn Moreels, is located in the city centre of Ghent, a port city in northwest Belgium. 
​.
​Evelyn Moreel’s modern take on traditional Parisian style in her own home is complete with the comfortable atmosphere she wanted to create for her family of five. As Evelyn puts it; “it’s a place that breathes nature and the finest materials in the midst of a city centre.”
​.
​Read more about Evelyn's home on estliving.com. 
​.
​Design @evelynmoreelsenteam
​Architecture @pascalbilquin 
​Photography @cafeine 
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/at-home-with-evelyn-moreels/

THE NEW FACES OF EST LIVING EDITORIAL | Karen McCartney
​.
We're proudly announcing the appointment of Karen McCartney (@mccartneyk) to the newly created role of editorial strategy advisor for estliving.com, est magazine and digital platforms.

​

​Photography @helenio_barbetta
​.

RESIDENTIAL DESIGN | AIDA Awards
​.
​Congratulations to @flackstudio_ for taking out the @auinteriordesignawards Residential Design award for their Potts Point House – a joint winner with @architectseat for their Bellows House in Flinders, Victoria. 
​.
A series of reveals throughout an 1930's home, @flackstudio_ principal and founder David Flack was tasked with ensuring the four-storey terrace in Potts Point, Sydney had continuity with the history of the city while guaranteeing practical, contemporary living for its owners. 
​.
​Read more about Potts Point in our feature on estliving.com – link in profile. 
​.
​Design @flackstudio_
​Photography @smartanson
​.

HOME TOUR | Casa Azul
.
The municipality of Grândola, located in Alentejo, is renowned for its red wine, vast olive groves and cork forests.
​.
​It’s here where a group of four friends decided to purchase four plots of land together, engaging Lisbon-based architecture firm @bakgordonarquitectos to sensitively construct a holiday home that appears as an extension of the arid landscape.
​.
​See more of this family holiday home on estliving.com – link in profile. 
​.
​Design @bakgordonarquitectos
​Photography @francisconogueira
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/casa-azul-bak-gordon/

node.text:
HOME TOUR | Harvey House 
​.
​@marmolradziner took on the weighted brief of restoring the Harvey House, originally designed by ​Buff & Hensman in 1969, located in Palm Springs, California.
​.
Originally designed to blur the boundaries between indoors and outdoors,  ​@marmolradziner introduced terrazzo as the primary material throughout the Harvey House, to accentuate the relationship between the home, pool and pool house, together with the expansive, floor-to-ceiling glazing. 
​.
​Design @marmolradziner
​Photography Roger Davies & Giorgio Possenti
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/

node.text:
KITCHEN OF THE MONTH | Above Board Living by Luigi Rosselli Architects
​.
The kitchen within @luigirosselliarchitects's recently completed ​Above Board Living project was our most popular for the month of August. 
​.
@luigirosselliarchitects designed 'Above Board Living' for a client passionate about design and their close proximity to Bronte Beach. 
​.
The rammed earth home takes its name from how the home is structured, where the main living areas and kitchen are all located on the upper level to make the most of the sea breeze and views below. 
​.
​See more of this project inside 'Spaces' on estliving.com – link in profile. 
​.
​Design @luigirosselliarchitects 
​Build @groundup_build

Styling @megan_morton
